$$
\displaystyle
S^2 = \frac 1 {n-1} \sum^n_{i=1}(x_i - \bar{x})^2.
$$

It differs from [[Biased Sample Variance]] in that it incorporates the [[Bessel's Correction]]:

$$
\displaystyle
S^2 = \left( \frac n {n-1} \right) S_n^2.
$$